<HL>
   Business Brief -- Chambers Development Co.:
   Permit Granted for Landfill
   In Somerset County, Pa.
</HL>
<DATE>
04/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7A
</SO>
<CO>
   CDVA
</CO>
<LP>
   Chambers Development Co., a Pittsburgh-based environmental
services concern, said it received a solid-waste permit from
the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Resources for a
34-acre landfill in Somerset County, Pa.
   With the permit, the landfill can accept an average of
2,200 tons a day of solid waste, Chambers said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it has permit applications pending for 37
acres at the Monroeville Landfill in Allegheny County, Pa.,
and for 82 acres at the Arden Landfill in Washington County,
Pa. It also has a pending application to reopen the Fulkroad
Landfill in Dauphin County, Pa.
</TEXT>
