<HL>
   Business Brief -- Cie. Generale d'Electricite:
   Unit Gets Phone-Gear Job
   From a Province in China
</HL>
<DATE>
04/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   F.CIU F.CGE FREST
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Alcatel N.V., a unit of Cie. Generale d'Electricite of
France, said it received a contract valued at 40 million
European currency units ($48.7 million) to provide digital
phone-switching equipment to the Chinese province of Sichuan.
   The order covers 300,000 lines of the company's System 12
digital switching, transmission equipment, telephone cables
and training. Alcatel's Spanish unit, Alcatel Standard
Electrica, received the order, bringing its contracts in
China to five with a total value of 80 million ECUs.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Madrid unit also got a two-phase contract totaling 54
million ECUs from Poland last week. The first phase covers
140,000 trunk lines of System 12 digital switching, and the
second covers 90,000 System 12 lines and transmission
equipment.
   Alcatel also said its 1989 profit rose 33% to 478 million
ECUs, on a 15% gain in revenue to 12.8 billion ECUs. Generale
d'Electricite previously reported 1989 consolidated earnings,
after payments to minority interests, of 4.94 billion francs
($878.6 million), on revenue of 143.9 billion francs.
</TEXT>
